snippet.textDisplay:
I discovered this song just a few days ago, and it’s quickly become one of the best songs I’ve ever heard.❣️
 The beauty of this track lies in its portrayal of how we make promises when we’re new in a relationship. Despite our best intentions, circumstances can change, and those bonds may end, even if we don’t want them to. As time passes, we mature and learn to accept how things were and how they are now. Yet, we still pray for that person and hold onto our love for them. The ending, with its harsh realities, truly resonates: "Jaa raha hoon me"

(For you all - I hope you all never lose the person you love. Even if everything seems to have gone wrong, remember that brighter days will come. Hold on to hope, because life has a way of bringing good things back around)
